## Opzioni per Dependency Injection in Spring

### 1. **Constructor Injection (Raccomandato)** ‚úÖ
```java
@Component
public class StartupMediator {

    private final GamificationService gamificationService;
    private final UserService userService;
    private final StartupPopupUIService popupUIService;

    // @Autowired √® opzionale se c'√® un solo costruttore
    public StartupMediator(GamificationService gamificationService, 
                          UserService userService, 
                          StartupPopupUIService popupUIService) {
        this.gamificationService = gamificationService;
        this.userService = userService;
        this.popupUIService = popupUIService;
    }
}
```

### 2. **Field Injection** ‚ö†Ô∏è
```java
@Component
public class StartupMediator {

    @Autowired
    private GamificationService gamificationService;

    @Autowired
    private UserService userService;

    @Autowired
    private StartupPopupUIService popupUIService;
}
```

### 3. **Setter Injection** üîÑ
```java
@Component
public class StartupMediator {

    private GamificationService gamificationService;
    private UserService userService;
    private StartupPopupUIService popupUIService;

    @Autowired
    public void setGamificationService(GamificationService gamificationService) {
        this.gamificationService = gamificationService;
    }

    @Autowired
    public void setUserService(UserService userService) {
        this.userService = userService;
    }

    @Autowired
    public void setPopupUIService(StartupPopupUIService popupUIService) {
        this.popupUIService = popupUIService;
    }
}
```

## Quando usare `@Autowired`

### **Constructor Injection**
- **Spring 4.3+**: `@Autowired` √® **opzionale** se c'√® un solo costruttore
- **Pi√π costruttori**: `@Autowired` √® **obbligatorio** per indicare quale usare
- **Raccomandato** perch√© garantisce immutabilit√† e fail-fast

### **Field/Setter Injection**
- `@Autowired` √® **sempre obbligatorio**
- Utile per dipendenze opzionali o configurazioni complesse

## Il tuo caso specifico

Nel tuo `StartupMediator` hai un problema:

```java
